						               													<description>Each game consists of 3 rounds. For each game, one player is the banker for 3 turns. He gives each player the coins: 2 coins of 10, 4 coins of 5, 10 coins of 2 and 20 coins of 1.&amp;#10;Each player deposits 2 coins into bowls 1-6 and the pot in the middle. The banker does the same but fills the pot up to 12 coins.&amp;#10;The banker begins to roll all 3 dice. Only 3 rounds are rolled. The give/take die determines whether the player has to deposit or withdraw money. The number die indicates the cup you pay into or receive from. The die with the eyes determines the amount of the win or the deposit.&amp;#10;Bowl 1 and 6: Doubles the bet. You pay or receive twice as much as you rolled eyes.&amp;#10;Double: In the case of a double, i.e. if the numbers on the number dice and the number dice are the same, the pot also plays. &amp;#10;If a bowl becomes empty during the 3 rounds, it is the banker's duty to refill it to the original deposit of all players. In return, the pot in the middle belongs to the banker after the end of the 3 rounds &amp;#10;Final round: When the 3 rounds have been rolled, the banker only starts with the number die. Each player now gets the total contents of the bowl he rolled. Play continues until all bowls are emptied. In the new game, the next player automatically becomes the banker.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
